      "content": "# CURRENT STEP SCOPE\n\n**Step 4 of 7**: Set maxConcurrency 1-2 and maxRequestRetries 3\n\n## Goal\n## Goal\nAdd `maxConcurrency` (set to 1) and `maxRequestRetries` (set to 3) to the PlaywrightCrawler options in `src/main.ts`.\n\n## Task Type\nModify existing code: update the crawler configuration object.\n\n## Technical Context from Codebase\n- `src/main.ts` line ~85–105 contains the crawler instantiation with options such as `proxyConfiguration`, `maxRequestsPerCrawl`, `launchContext`, `preNavigationHooks`, etc.\n- Current options do not include `maxConcurrency` or `maxRequestRetries`; Crawlee defaults are used (concurrency is automatically managed, retries default to 0 or 1 depending on crawler version).\n- The actor uses PlaywrightCrawler from `@crawlee/playwright`.\n- No input schema fields exist yet for these values; they will be hardcoded now and can be exposed later in the optional **extend-input-schema** step.\n\n## Action\nIn `src/main.ts`, locate the object passed to `new PlaywrightCrawler({...})`. Add the following properties:\n- `maxConcurrency: 1` (or 2 if appropriate; use 1 for a more human-like, less aggressive crawl).\n- `maxRequestRetries: 3`.\n\nDo NOT add `useSessionPool` or `sessionPoolOptions`—those belong to a separate step.\n\n## Reasoning\n- `maxConcurrency: 1` reduces parallelism to mimic a single user browsing, preventing detection as a scraper.\n- `maxRequestRetries: 3` ensures transient failures (e.g., timeouts, 5xx) are retried with Crawlee’s built-in exponential backoff, improving robustness without custom logic.\n- Hardcoding is acceptable now; later steps will make these values configurable via input schema if needed.\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Open `src/main.ts`.\n- Find the `new PlaywrightCrawler({` call. Inside the options object, add these lines (order does not matter):\n  ```typescript\n  maxConcurrency: 1,\n  maxRequestRetries: 3,\n  ```\n- Ensure the commas are correct and TypeScript compiles.\n- No other files need modification.\n\n## Error Handling and Edge Cases\n- If `maxConcurrency` is set too low for large input lists, the crawl may take longer; this is acceptable for stealth.\n- If `maxRequestRetries` is 3, ensure the `retryOnBlocked` (if used) is not overridden; Crawlee automatically retries on network errors.\n- No special error handling needed—these are simple numeric properties.\n\n## Validation\n- Run `npm run build` (or `npx tsc --noEmit`) to ensure TypeScript compiles.\n- Run the integration test `npx vitest run` to verify the crawler starts and completes with the new settings.\n- Manually inspect that `maxConcurrency` and `maxRequestRetries` appear in the crawler options (e.g., by logging the crawler instance after creation, or checking debug output).\n\n## Dependencies and Inputs\n- This step depends only on the existing `src/main.ts` file.\n- No new npm dependencies.\n\n## Constraints\n- Do not change `useSessionPool` or any other options not in this step’s scope.\n- Use numeric literals exactly `1` and `3`.\n- Follow existing code style (indentation, commas, etc.).\n- Commit only this change; do not modify tests or input schema.\n\nThis is the ONLY task you must complete in this iteration. Do not work on other steps.",
